    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This E46 M3 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated engineering, featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six equipped with individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing. The powertrain is mated to a crisp Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission, delivering linear torque across a broad power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Mechanically, the vehicle is superlative: the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, and both the rod bearings and VANOS system have undergone comprehensive preventative overhauls to ensure peak reciprocating assembly integrity. The chassis remains taut, utilizing a Variable M Differential Lock for optimal lateral traction and turn-in precision. Finished in a concours-level exterior with zero oxidation or clear coat failure, this example offers a visceral, analog driving experience that modern electronically-assisted platforms cannot replicate.",
